text.__SUMMARY__:
Eucalyptus ultima is a mallee that is native to a small area in the Gascoyne region of Western Australia.The mallee typically grows to a height of 2.5 to 7 metres (8 to 23 ft) and has smooth bark. It blooms between July and August producing inflorescences with white-cream coloured flowers.
It is found on rocky rises and scree slopes around Exmouth in the Gascoyne region where it grows in skeletal soils over limestone.
